% Bibliographic source of truth for the CV publications.
%
% This file drives BOTH the LaTeX CVs (via biblatex + biber) and the website.
% After editing it, run `python scripts/generate_cvs.py`, which
%   1. compiles the per-variant CV PDFs with biblatex/biber, and
%   2. regenerates src/data/publications.json that the website consumes.
%
% Conventions
%   keywords    CV-variant filtering (atomistic / agents / finance / industry)
%               plus the literal `icml2026` marker for the "Presenting at
%               ICML 2026" section. biblatex filters on these; the website
%               generator reads them to split the sections.
%   url         primary link the title points to on the website.
%   note        for ICML workshop posters, the session time; printed by
%               biblatex and used as the link text for `sessionurl` on the web.
%   sessionurl  custom field (declared in the CV template's data model): the
%               ICML virtual session page. Website-only; not printed in the PDF.
%   addendum    trailing remark (e.g. authorship order), printed by biblatex
%               and bolded on the website.

